                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-807" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD THORPE</persName>
                  </hi>. I saw the prisoner with the bottle in his hand—he said, I have found this here, you can have it for a pint of beer"—he said, "Per-haps you will take my baggage"—I found he had got no baggage—the captain asked if he had paid his fare—he said he had, and had lost the ticket—he had no money on him—I found the knife-case lodged on the paper in the water-closet.</p>
